\frac{\partial^2 y} {\partial x^2}   = \lim_{\Delta x \to 0} \frac {1} {\Delta x}                           \left(\frac{\partial y} {\partial x}_x - \frac{\partial y} {\partial x}_{x+ \Delta x}\right)
 \frac{\partial y} {\partial x}_x 
 \frac{\partial^2 y}{\partial x^2}  = \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left[ \frac{\partial y}{\partial x} \right]  = \lim_{\Delta x \to 0} \frac{\left.\frac{\partial y}{\partial x}\right|_{x+\Delta_x}                               - \left.\frac{\partial y}{\partial x}\right|_x}{\Delta x} 
 f''(x) = \frac{df'(x)}{dx} = \lim_{\Delta x \to 0} \frac{f'(x+\Delta x) - f'(x)}{\Delta x}. 
